The Chronicle PRESIDENT Emmerson Mnangagwa on Thursday held a meeting with the Matabeleland Collective at the State House in Bulawayo. Matabeleland Collective, an organisation comprising of churches and civic society organisations from Bulawayo, Matabeleland North and South Provinces, had requested for a meeting with President Mnangagwa to discuss among other things, development issues in the region. The President hailed the organisation for leading in engagement for the development of the country promising to avail himself for future interactions of a similar nature. More to followâ€¦ 